<br>
As for my personal grudges, I think I made that totally clear.  I have no grudge against IG or you.  I work with people from IG quite regularly, and I think if you ask any of them they'll vouch for me.<br>
<br>
My grudge is with the system that is currently in place which resulted in this unfortunate confrontation.  I'd like to see it discussed and changed.  I don't think that the thread should be closed because it seems to me that would just be further ignoring of the problem.<br>
<br>
I said it at least twice now.  I don't fault IG specifically any more than any other guild that has done the same thing when their turn for CT or any other rotation mob came up.  IG worked within the system that is in place for them, and I think that system could use some work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ustryfe002.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stryfe002</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(12/10/01 8:13:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is simple, really</span><hr size=1> Ok, taking back my request to close, as the door has kind of opened...<br>
<br>
I agree, the system can use some work...the IGB is not perfect, but it works quite well for the higher level guilds, but it fails to address certain things like Fear, Hate, Kael, whatever, these are considered FFA...But think about it, the IGB wasnt designed for this...it skipped the fact that certain things can conflict (Inno/Hate, CT/Fear, Tunare/PoG (when the time comes) etc)...How can these situations be fielded w/o redesigning and reconstructing the IGB process and w/o corrupting, the already difficult at times, system? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uirdanar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Irdanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(12/10/01 8:24:32 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://rpgpics.simplenet.com/EQ/Zerg4.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is simple, really</span><hr size=1> Through communication from the IGB guild slated for said mobs.<br>
<br>
Innoruuk is not on rotation btw.  Most IGB guilds only kill him out of boredom between rotations, and I can tell you for sure the only reason ML even goes into PoH anymore is for a couple of Epic drops that have eluded some members for 8+ months.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, it doesn't take much to work somethiing out with a guild slated for, say, CT.  Use tells, find an Officer, and get a resolution.  If you absolutely *must* have the plane to yourself, it's not going happen, I'm sorry.  Deal with it, or push it back a day.  However, I can tell you right now, going in there with one of those guilds is probably the best thing that can happen to your guild, especially your first 4-5 runs.  You're basically able to go in there with the Barry Bonds and Tiger Woods of Druzzil RO, take advantage of it, rather than being self righteous and vindictive on this board or others. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15408">Quintall Dys'Raydin</a><BR>
